\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:tangency"

\end_inset

, which is a first order condition, we can define the following identity:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v'(x_{1}^{*})\equiv\frac{p_{1}}{p_{2}}v'(x_{2}^{*}),
\]

\end_inset

differentiating both sides of the identity with regards to 
\begin_inset Formula $w$
\end_inset

 we get:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v''(x_{1}^{*})\cdot\frac{dx_{1}^{*}}{dw}\equiv\frac{p_{1}}{p_{2}}v''(x_{2}^{*})\cdot\frac{dx_{2}^{*}}{dw}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

